tool_description: Code against the Bitbucket API to automate simple tasks, embed Bitbucket data into your own site, build mobile or desktop apps
name: Bitbucket
title: Bitbucket

api_list.name: addBranchRestrictions
api_list.description: Creates a new branch restriction rule for a repository.

required_parameters.name: kind
required_parameters.description: kind describes what will be restricted. Allowed values are: push, force, delete, and restrict_merges.

optional_parameters.name: value
optional_parameters.description: Value with kind-specific semantics: "require_approvals_to_merge" uses it to require a minimum number of approvals on a PR; "require_passing_builds_to_merge" uses it to require a minimum number of passing builds.

api_list.name: addCommitBuild
api_list.description: Creates a new build status against the specified commit.

required_parameters.name: url
required_parameters.description: A URL linking back to the vendor or build system, for providing more information about whatever process produced this status.

required_parameters.name: key
required_parameters.description: An identifier for the status that's unique to its type (current "build" is the only supported type) and the vendor, e.g. BB-DEPLOY

required_parameters.name: state
required_parameters.description: Provides some indication of the status of this commit

optional_parameters.name: description
optional_parameters.description: A description of the build (e.g. "Unit tests in Bamboo")

optional_parameters.name: name
optional_parameters.description: An identifier for the build itself, e.g. BB-DEPLOY-1

optional_parameters.name: refname
optional_parameters.description: The name of the ref that pointed to this commit at the time the status object was created. Note that this the ref may since have moved off of the commit.
